# Cigarettes After Sex

From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia

Jump to: navigation, search

Cigarettes After Sex  
---  
Origin | [El Paso, Texas](/wiki/El_Paso,_Texas "El Paso, Texas"), US  
Genres | 

  * [Dream pop](/wiki/Dream_pop "Dream pop")[1]
  * [shoegaze](/wiki/Shoegaze "Shoegaze")[2]
  * [ambient pop](/wiki/Ambient_pop "Ambient pop")[3]
  * [slowcore](/wiki/Slowcore "Slowcore")[4]

  
Years active | 2008–present  
Labels | [Partisan](/wiki/Partisan_Records "Partisan Records")  
Website | [cigarettesaftersex.com](http://cigarettesaftersex.com/)  
Members | 

  * Greg Gonzalez

Past members |

**Cigarettes After Sex** is an American [ambient pop](/wiki/Ambient_pop
"Ambient pop") band from [El Paso, Texas](/wiki/El_Paso,_Texas "El Paso,
Texas"), formed in 2008 by Greg Gonzalez. The band's debut EP, _I._ , was
released in 2012 with the singles "Affection" and "K." following in 2015 and
2016, respectively. Their first full-length record, _[Cigarettes After
Sex](/wiki/Cigarettes_After_Sex_\(album\) "Cigarettes After Sex \(album\)")_ ,
was released on June 9, 2017.

##
History[[edit](/w/index.php?title=Cigarettes_After_Sex&action=edit&section=1
"Edit section: History")]

Cigarettes After Sex was formed in [El Paso, Texas](/wiki/El_Paso,_Texas "El
Paso, Texas"), in 2008.[5][6][7] Gonzalez recorded the first EP, _I._ , in a
four-story stairway at his alma mater, University of Texas at El Paso, calling
the experience "basically an accident; kind of an experiment".[7] "Nothing's
Gonna Hurt You Baby", "I'm a Firefighter", "Dreaming of You", and "Starry
Eyes" were recorded for _I._

Gonzalez relocated to [Brooklyn](/wiki/Brooklyn "Brooklyn"), New York, where
the band's single "Affection" was recorded and released in 2015 along with a
cover of [REO Speedwagon](/wiki/REO_Speedwagon "REO Speedwagon")'s "[Keep On
Loving You](/wiki/Keep_On_Loving_You_\(song\) "Keep On Loving You
\(song\)")".[8][9]

Through music recommendations, Cigarettes After Sex has gained millions of
views on YouTube, leading to live performances across Europe, Asia, and the
US. Cigarettes After Sex released their [self-titled debut studio
album](/wiki/Cigarettes_After_Sex_\(album\) "Cigarettes After Sex \(album\)")
on June 9, 2017.[10][7][11]

"Nothing's Gonna Hurt You Baby" was featured in episode 7 of the first season
of _[The Handmaid's Tale](/wiki/The_Handmaid%27s_Tale_\(TV_series\) "The
Handmaid's Tale \(TV series\)")_.[12][13], episode 7 of _[The
Sinner](/wiki/The_Sinner_\(TV_series\) "The Sinner \(TV series\)")_ [14], and
episode 9 of the eighth season of
_[Shameless](/wiki/Shameless_\(U.S._TV_series\) "Shameless \(U.S. TV
series\)")_.[15]

## Musical style and
influences[[edit](/w/index.php?title=Cigarettes_After_Sex&action=edit&section=2
"Edit section: Musical style and influences")]

In a feature for Noisey by _Vice_ , Christina Cacouris describes Cigarettes
After Sex as "elemental, hazy and romantic, but with a noir edge underneath
Gonzalez's androgynous voice" as well as "sweet and sentimental".[7] "As the
band’s name suggests, it’s reminiscent of lying in bed, but its ambient
qualities don’t prevent it from being music you can dance to."[7] Gonzalez
cites [Françoise Hardy](/wiki/Fran%C3%A7oise_Hardy "Françoise Hardy") as his
favorite singer and [Miles Davis](/wiki/Miles_Davis "Miles Davis") as having
great impact.[7] The band also includes The Cowboy Junkies' album _[The
Trinity Session](/wiki/The_Trinity_Session "The Trinity Session")_ , [Julee
Cruise](/wiki/Julee_Cruise "Julee Cruise"), and [Cocteau
Twins](/wiki/Cocteau_Twins "Cocteau Twins") as influences.[6][16] The music
blog Eardrums Music describes the band as "slow, dreamy and beautiful with
gorgeous, tender vocals and very good lyrics." and compares it to [Mazzy
Star](/wiki/Mazzy_Star "Mazzy Star")[16] Music bloggers behind [Swell
Tone](http://swelltonemusic.com/about/) describe Cigarettes After Sex as a
band producing "melancholy, slow pop that will sweetly rock any listener into
a listless stupor."[17]

Reviewing _Affection_ for
[Independentmusicnews.com](http://independentmusicnews.com/), Jae Pyl
concludes that "there’s just such an intimacy to Cigarettes After Sex's sound
that it’s impossible to not let it into the pit of your belly."[9]

##
Members[[edit](/w/index.php?title=Cigarettes_After_Sex&action=edit&section=3
"Edit section: Members")]

Since inception in 2008, the group has included a number of different members
and collaborators led by Greg Gonzalez:[8]

**Current members** :

  * Greg Gonzalez – founder, lead vocals, electric guitar, acoustic guitar, bass
  * Phillip Tubbs – keyboards, electric guitar
  * Randall Miller – bass
  * Jacob Tomsky – drums

**Previous members** :

  * Greg Leah – drums
  * Steve Herrada – keyboards
  * Emily Davis – acoustic guitar
